            <biogHist>
                <p>John Black was born to John Black, farmer and Flora née MacIntyre. Little is
                    known of his life, but he is recorded in the 1871 Census as a pauper living with
                    his daughter Isabella (56), granddaughter Sarah Leith (26), a domestic servant,
                    and great-granddaughter Isabella Black (8 months), living in Killan, Lismore.
                    Prior to the census Carmichael had met him in September 1870 and he related the
                    location of Dòmhnall an Dannsair's house at Killechiarain [Kilcheran]. </p>
                <p>John died in April 1872 from natural causes and his nephew Hugh Black signed the
                    death certificate.</p>
